The article emphasizes the importance of implementing vaccination requirements and testing protocols to protect workers, particularly in light of the highly transmissible Omicron variant in the US. The author asserts that the Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) vaccination or testing rule is crucial in ensuring that employers prioritize the safety of their employees. Similarly, the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services (CMS) health care vaccination requirement aims to safeguard patients by compelling healthcare providers to adhere to vaccination protocols. The author expresses confidence in the legal authority of both policies and states that the Department of Justice (DOJ) will vigorously defend them at the Supreme Court.